===Glyph origin===
{{liushu|ic}} – (⿱丵臼*) A chisel inside of a mortar, an ancient form of {{zh-l|*鑿}}, dating back to oracle bone inscriptions, components such as {{zh-l|*殳}} and {{zh-l|*金}} were added later.

{{Han-glyphref|⿱丵凵}}
Used as a shorthand in popular novels of the Qing dynasty.

Eventually adopted as an official simplified character by the People's Republic of China in the 1956 {{w|Chinese Character Simplification Scheme}}. <!-- Refer https://zh.wikisource.org/wiki/漢字簡化方案 -->

